DataElement.preferredName: Image Feature Data Data Property or Attribute java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: In image processing, a piece of information which is relevant for solving the computational task related to a certain application, either specific structures in the image itself (e.g., simple structures such as points or edges to more complex structures such as objects) or the result of a general neighborhood operation (feature extractor or feature detector) applied to the image.:A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn._A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn.:The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspect of a person, object, action, process, or substance._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
